# PowerShell and CMD Rules

Use PowerShell first.

Required script behavior:
1. Use fixed project root when safety matters.
2. Use Test-Path before file operations.
3. Use New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force for folders.
4. Back up existing files before overwriting.
5. Write logs.
6. Print status messages.
7. Avoid destructive commands.
8. Do not use Remove-Item -Recurse -Force without explicit approval.
9. Do not modify production logic from automation scripts in this phase.
